HEADWORD: Scorify
<hw>Sco"ri*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Scorified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Scorifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[<ets>Scoria</ets> + <ets>-fy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>scorifier</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To reduce to scoria
or slag; specifically, in assaying, to fuse so as to separate the gangue
and earthy material, with borax, lead, soda, etc., thus leaving the gold
and silver in a lead button; hence, to separate from, or by means of, a
slag.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scorious</ent>⟦br⟧
